OUT! CAUGHT! South Africa have won the match by an inning and 236 and have done a clean sweep in the series! Tossed it up and around middle, from wide of the crease, Tanaka Chivanga goes across and looks to paddle it fine. But gets a top edge that lobs up over the keeper behind the wickets. Wiaan Mulder quickly moves to his left from first slip and pouches it. That has been a thumping win for SA.
Tanaka Chivanga c W Mulder b S Muthusamy 22 (26b 3x4 1x6)
Full and around off, Tanaka Chivanga pushes it back to the bowler.
Around off, Tanaka Chivanga comes forward to defend it but gets an inside edge towards fine leg.
Punched down to cover off the back foot.
On the pads, nudged it to mid-wicket.
Nagging length and around off, Wellington Masakadza goes to cut it but misses.
Full and around off, pushed away towards mid off.
FOUR! Another good shot! Flighted, full and outside off, Wellington Masakadza goes across and lofts it inside out over covers for a boundary.
Full and around off, knocked it down to long on for one.
Full and around off, Wellington Masakadza comes forward and nudges it to mid-wicket.
Nagging length and around off, Wellington Masakadza punches it it to mid off.
Around off, pushed away to wide long off for one.
FOUR! And another! Full and around off, Tanaka Chivanga takes a step forward and heaves it off the inner half of the bat aerially towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Swept away! Tossed it up and on the pads, Tanaka Chivanga goes across on his knees and sweeps it fine to deep backward square leg for a boundary.
Around off, defended it to mid-wicket off the front foot.
Back of a length and down the leg side, Wellington Masakadza sways away from it.
FOUR! Nicely done! Full and around off, Wellington Masakadza comes forward and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Down the leg side, Wellington Masakadza lets it go.
On a length and around leg, Wellington Masakadza looks to flick it but misses. The ball clips his pad and rolls away to mid-wicket.
A bouncer, Wellington Masakadza ducks under it.
Full and around off, Wellington Masakadza comes forward and defends it.
In the stumps, blocked out back to the bowler.
Around off, Tanaka Chivanga defends it.
Full and around middle, Tanaka Chivanga goes to sweep it but misses.
Nagging length and around off, Wellington Masakadza knocks it down to long on for one.
Darts in down the leg side, Wellington Masakadza pads it away and the ball rolls away towards fine leg. They take two leg byes but the umpire declines it as he hasn't offered any shot.
Tossed it up, around off, Wellington Masakadza comes forward and drives it to cover.
Full and around off, driven to mid off.
A bouncer, follows the batter, Tanaka Chivanga gets surprised and looks to sway away from it but falls down in the process.
Back of a length, around off, Tanaka Chivanga remains crouched and looks to upper-cut it but missses.
Angles it in the stumps, Tanaka Chivanga defends it.
Hard length, over off, Tanaka Chivanga taps it down to cover.
Full and outside off, stays a bit low, Tanaka Chivanga shoulders his arms.
Similar delivery, outside off, blocked out.
Outside off, Wellington Masakadza goes across and defends it.
Much full and around off, blocked again.
Full and around off, defended back to the bowler.
On the pads, flicked away to deep mid-wicket for one.
Around off, blocked out.
EDGED AND FOUR! Full and around off, Wellington Masakadza comes forward and looks to drive it but gets a big outside edge that goes through the gap between third slip and gully for a boundary.
WIDE! A bouncer goes above the head of the batter, Wellington Masakadza ducks under it. Called a wide.
Full and around off, Wellington Masakadza nudges it towards mid on.
Another bouncer, Wellington Masakadza ducks underneath it.

Corbin Bosch goes in celeb appeal and thinks, the match is done but the umpire shakes his head! A well-directed bouncer, around middle, Wellington Masakadza tries to sway away from it, but the ball follows him, and though he tries to bring his bat up to defend, but misses. The ball clips his shoulder and goes behind the wickets, where the keeper pouches it.
Back of a length and around middle, Wellington Masakadza hops back and nudges it to mid-wicket.
Bowls it full and around off, Wellington Masakadza turns it towards mid on.
Nagging length and around off, Tanaka Chivanga punches it to cover off the back foot.
Full and around middle, Tanaka Chivanga uses his feet but gets yorked himself. Adjusts his shot and digs it out towards mid-wicket.
Nagging length and outside off, left alone.
SIX! Hammered! Full and around off, Tanaka Chivanga goes across, on his knees and muscles it over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
On the pads, swept away to square leg.
FOUR! Oh, wow! Tossed it up and around off, Tanaka Chivanga clears out his front leg away and smokes it down the ground over the bowler's head for a boundary.
Lands it full and outside off, Tanaka Chivanga drives it towards cover point for one.

OUT! CAUGHT! Zimbabwe are nine down and Corbin Bosch picks up his fourth wicket! Bowls it on the back of a length, and keeps the line around the off stump. Gets an extra bounce off the deck and Blessing Muzarabani presses back to defend it but gets a bit surprised. The ball follows him and he only manages to get an outside edge that goes to the right of third slip, where Lesego Senokwane puts in a dive there and pouches it with both hands. South Africa are now just one wicket away, and this session can get extended if they don't get in scheduled time.
Blessing Muzarabani c L Senokwane b C Bosch 0 (11b 0x4 0x6)
Back of a length and around middle, Wellington Masakadza pulls it down to deep backward square leg for one.
Nagging length, around off, blocked out.

A massive appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes his head! A touch full and around off, Wellington Masakadza comes forward to defend it but gets an inside edge onto his front pad. Also, the ball gets stuck in the gap around his pad. Height could the issue!
Full and around off, driven away to cover point off the front foot.
BEATEN! Slower and on the tempted length, just outside off, Blessing Muzarabani comes forward to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full and straight, blocked out.
On the pads, tucked it to mid-wicket off the back foot.
Nagging length and around off, Blessing Muzarabani goes back and punches it to cover.
Around off, pushes it away towards cover point.
Very full and around off, blocked out towards mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, sliced away to gully by Wellington Masakadza.
On middle, tucked it to mid-wicket.

A nasty one! Short of a length, around off, angles in the body of the batter, Wellington Masakadza gets cramped as the ball follows him and he looks to bring his bat around his face to defend but misses. He closes his eyes off the ball and gets hit on his right shoulder.
Full and around off, Wellington Masakadza comes forward to defend it but gets it off the inner half of the bat to mid-wicket.
Hard length and outside off, Wellington Masakadza pats it down to cover.
On a good length and around off, Wellington Masakadza comes forward and taps it towards cover point.
Around off, slower, Blessing Muzarabani goes to defend it off the front foot but gets beaten on the outside edge.

Floated up and around middle, Blessing Muzarabani comes forward to defend it but gets an inside edge onto his front pad and the ball lobs up and beats the short leg fielder to his right. Rolls away towards square leg.
On the pads, flicked away to deep square leg for one.
Nagging length and around off, Wellington Masakadza goes back and slices it to second slip on the bounce.
Similar length, around off, defended it to cover off the front foot.
Tossed it up and around off, Wellington Masakadza comes forward and blocks it.
Around off, defended back to the bowler.
On a length and around off, Blessing Muzarabani blocks it out.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! This is amazing bowling from Corbin Bosch. Bowls it on a good length and from wide of the crease to create an inward angle, and keeps the line around off. Kundai Matigimu plants his front leg forward and looks to defend it but plays the inside line and also gets a bit late to bring his bat down in time. The ball straightens out after pitching and goes with pace to beat the underedge of the bat and rattles the off stump. Zimbabwe are eight down and South Africa are just two wickets away.
Kundai Matigimu b C Bosch 0 (3b 0x4 0x6)
A bit full and around off, blocked out by Kundai Matigimu.
Nagging length and outside off, Kundai Matigimu leaves it.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! The skipper of Zimbabwe goes back and they are seven down. Corbin bowls it full and outside off, and lures the batter to go for a drive. Craig Ervine comes forward and looks to just push it into the off side for a single to complete his milestone but plays it with soft hands. The ball isn't that full, and the batter only manages to get an outside edge that goes behind the wickets, where the keeper, Kyle Verreynne, moves to his left a bit and pouches it around his chest height. A big wicket for South Africa as they are just three wickets away from a big win.
Craig Ervine (c) c K Verreynne b C Bosch 49 (95b 6x4 0x6)
Flighted, full and around off, Wellington Masakadza comes forward to flick it but gets an inside edge towards square leg.
Full and around off, Wellington Masakadza pushes it back to the bowler.
On the pads, Wellington Masakadza looks to flick it but gets an inside edge onto his front pad.
Loud appeal for caught behind by the keeper but the umpire shakes his head! Nagging length and outside off, turns away, Wellington Masakadza looks to cut it off the back foot but misses.
Dragged length and outside off, Craig Ervine cuts it to deep point for one.
Full and around off, flicked it to mid on.
Around off, defended it to cover.
Full and outside off, Wellington Masakadza leaves it.
Sliding on the pads, tucked it to square leg.
Back of a length and outside off, left alone.
Short to the fielder! On a length and outside off, Wellington Masakadza looks to push it but gets an outside edge that goes on the bounce to the gully fielder who stops it to his left.
Begins with a full ball, around off, Wellington Masakadza comes forward and slices it towards point.
Floated up and around off, Craig Ervine comes forward and defends it right under his eyes.
Nagging length and around off, Craig Ervine pushes it to cover off the back foot.
In the stumps, blocked out towards cover.
Tossed it up and around off, Craig Ervine comes forward and tucks it to mid-wicket.
Around off, defended back to the bowler.
Full and around off, Craig Ervine pats it down to backward point.
Around off, punched down to cover off the front foot.
Nagging length and around off, Wellington Masakadza defends it solidly off the back foot.
Almost a yorker, outside off, Wellington Masakadza jams it out towards cover.
BEATEN! Full and outside off, Wellington Masakadza comes forward and looks to flick it but plays the wrong line. Gets beaten on the outside edge.
Sliding on the pads, Wellington Masakadza tickles it fine towards deep fine leg for a couple of runs to get off the mark.
Back of a length and around off, Craig Ervine pulls it down to deep square leg for one.
Around off, pushed down back to the bowler off the front foot.
Outside off, defended to covers.
Full and outside off, Wellington Masakadza brings his pad and defends it.

NOT OUT! Wellington Masakadza survives a close call! Tossed it up, slower and around off, Wellington Masakadza is drawn forward into his defence and he looks to play down with a straight bat but gets beaten on the outside edge. The keeper collects it to his left behind the wickets and whips the bails off as the batter lifts off his back foot of the crease. It is referred upstairs, and the third umpire checks the replays from different angles. He gives his verdict as not-out as the back foot of the batter was down when the keeper took off the bails. As there is no conclusive evidence to turn the decision and he gives NOT OUT.
Dragged length and around off, Craig Ervine punches it to long on off the back foot for one.
Outside off, pushed away to cover.
On the good length and around off, defended back to the right of the bowler.
Down the leg side, Wellington Masakadza misses his flick shot.

Edged but short! On a good length and around off, Wellington Masakadza comes forward to defend it and plays it with soft hands. Gets an outside edge but the ball falls down ahead of the second slip fielder.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another goes down, and South Africa are just four wickets away from a clean sweep now! A bit fuller but not that full, around middle, tries to attack the stumps, Tafadzwa Tsiga prods forward and looks to defend it but gets a bit late in his shot and ends up chipping it aerially to mid-wicket. Lesego Senokwane takes a simple catch around his chest height and Zimbabwe are six down. A soft dismissal for the batter, but Codi Yusuf has executed his strategies to perfection and picks up his second wickets of the inning.
Tafadzwa Tsiga (wk) c L Senokwane b C Yusuf 1 (20b 0x4 0x6)
Nagging length and outside off, punched down to cover.
Back of a length and around middle, Craig Ervine drags it down to deep fine leg for one.
Same line and length, around off, Tafadzwa Tsiga defends it off the back foot.
Around off, defended it to cover.
Short and around off, pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and around off, Craig Ervine sweeps it to deep square leg for one.
Nagging length and around middle, Craig Ervine tucks it to mid-wicket.
Around off, defended back to the bowler. Oh, Senuran Muthusamy has overstepped and it is called a NO BALL.

FOUR! A good shot from the skipper! Tossed it up and around middle, Craig Ervine changes his stance and reverse-sweeps it towards deep backward point. The fielder there tries to cut it off but can't save the boundary.
Nagging length, around off, punched down to mid on.
Back of a length and angling in, around middle, Tafadzwa Tsiga turns it towards mid on off the back foot.
Again a short-pitched delivery, outside off, Tafadzwa Tsiga sways away from it.
Short of a length and around off, Tafadzwa Tsiga ducks underneath it.
On the good length and around off, Tafadzwa Tsiga tucks it to mid-wicket.
Around off, driven towards mid off for a quick single.

There is confusion between the batters but no harm is done! Full and around off, Tsiga pushes it to mid off and is caught ball-watching, but Ervine wants to have a single as he leaves his crease and takes some steps forward, but is sent back by Tsiga. Brevis collects the ball and makes a throw to the non-striker's end but misses.
Dragged length, around off, blocked out.
Another edge found! Full and around off, Tafadzwa Tsiga plants his front leg forward to defend it but gets an outside edge that rolls away past the first slip to his right.
BEATEN! Much slower and on the dragged length, just outside off, turns away, Tafadzwa Tsiga comes forward to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Around off, defended back to the bowler.
Slower, full and around middle, tucked it to mid-wicket.
Again pitches it full and around off, Craig gets squared up but manages to keep it out towards cover.
Full and coming in with the angle, around leg, Craig Ervine misses his flick shot and gets rapped on the front pad. There is an appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes his head. Could be going down leg.
Nagging length and outside off, Craig Ervine punches it to cover.
Sliding on the pads, flicked it to square leg off the front foot.
BEATEN! On a good length and in that channel outside off, moves away a touch, Craig Ervine comes forward to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Hard length and around middle, Craig flicks it to mid on.
On the shorter side and around middle, Craig turns it towards fine leg for one.
Flighted, full and around middle, Tafadzwa Tsiga looks to defend it but gets an inside edge towards square leg. A single taken.
Nagging length and around leg, Craig tickles it down to deep fine leg for one.
Around middle, defended it to the left of the bowler.
On the pads, flicked it to mid-wicket.
Floated up and around off, Craig Ervine comes forward to defend it but gets an inside edge that rolls away through the gap between pad and the leg stump.
Similar length and around off, blocked out by Tsiga.
Around off, pushed it down to covers.
Back of a length and around off, defended towards mid-wicket.

OUT! LBW! Codi Yusuf gets his first and Zimbabwe are five down! Bowls it on the hard length and around off, gets it skid away from the surface. Wessly Madhevere is caught in his crease as he remains in two minds whether to play it on the front foot or the back foot. He chooses the former one and looks to defend it with a straight bat. But the ball nips back in sharply and beats the outside edge of the bat and hits him on the front pad. An appeal goes up for LBW and the umpire obliges. Wessly Madhevere walks back and Zimbabwe are under the sink now as they lose their half of the side. South Africa are just cruising at the moment in this session or to say, in this match whole.
Wessly Madhevere lbw C Yusuf 5 (9b 0x4 0x6)
Nagging length and outside off, left alone.
Sliding on the pads, Craig Ervine tickles it to deep fine leg for one.
Much straighter, around off, defended towards cover.
Around off, blocked out.

A tough chance goes down! Floated up and around off, Wessly Madhevere comes forward and looks to go downtown but miscues it off the cue end of the bat. The ball skews up towards mid on, where the substitute fielder, Zubayr Hamza, backtracks it and tries to fetch out with his extended right arm but he is in no position to take it. The ball goes through his hand and they take two runs.
Around off, pushed away to covers off the front foot.
BEATEN! Tempting length and just outside off, turns away, Wessly Madhevere is drawn forward into his defence but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Tossed it up and around middle, Wessly Madhevere goes across on his knees and looks to sweep it but gets a top edge that flies over the keeper behind the wickets. Two runs taken.

Sliding on the pads, on the fuller length, Craig misses his flick shot as his head falls over. Gets hit on the front pad and there is an appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes his head. Could be going down leg.

FOUR! This is a good shot! On a good length and around middle and leg, Craig Ervine comes forward and just tickles it fine to deep fine leg. The deep fine leg fielder runs across to his left and even puts in a dive but can't save the boundary.
On the length, around leg, Craig Ervine misses his flick shot.
Around off, defended back to the bowler.
On the pads, tickled down to deep fine leg for one.

Oh, just short! On a good length, from around the wicket and around off, Craig Ervine prods forward and just pushes at it but gets a big outside edge that flies flat towards the gully fielder, who moves to his left but the ball falls down ahead of him and goes through him towards third man. Three runs taken.

OUT! CAUGHT! Senuran Muthusamy has his man, finally and this time, Mulder makes no mistake, so that dropped catch hasn't cost much to South Africa. Gives flight and pitches it full and around off, Nick Welch takes a step forward and looks to flick it. He gets undone by turn and drift and just manages to get a leading edge that goes towards slip, where Wiaan Mulder moves to his right a bit and pouches this low catch around his waist height. Zimbabwe are four down and a set batter, Nick Welch, is gone after playing a good hand of 55 runs.
Nick Welch c W Mulder b S Muthusamy 55 (126b 3x4 2x6)
On the shorter side and around off, Nick Welch pushes it back to the bowler.
Around off, defended back to the bowler off the front foot.
Dragged length and around off, Craig Ervine goes back and turns it with soft hands to deep square leg for one.
On the pads, tucked it to square leg.
Tossed it up and around middle, flicked away to mid-wicket.
Nagging length and around off, blocked out towards cover off the front foot.
Oh, close to get chopped on! Hard length and around off, Nick Welch goes to defend it with gets an underedge and the ball rolls past the off stump back to the keeper.
On a length and outside off, left alone again.
Similar length and line, outside off, Nick leaves it alone again.
On the good length and around the fourth stump line, stays a bit low, Nick lets it go.
Nagging length and outside off, Nick Welch shoulders his arms.
FOUR! SWEPT AWAY! Full and around off, Craig Ervine goes across on his knees and sweeps it aerially towards deep square leg for a boundary.
Around off, blocked out.
Sliding on the pads, swept away to deep fine leg for a couple of runs.

EDGED AND DROPPED! The skipper Wiaan Mulder is the culprit. Probably, the first error he has made in this match! Tossed it up and around off, got some drift off the deck as well. Nick Welch is drawn forward into his defence but gets an outside edge that goes low to the right of slip, where Mulder tries to move there and gets his hands on it but can't hold onto it. A single is taken as the ball rolls away towards third man.
On the pads, eased down to long on for one.
Much full and around middle, Nick Welch skips out the crease and drills it to long on for one.
Around off, Craig Ervine pushes it to cover. That will be LUNCH ON DAY 3!
Full and around middle, Nick again uses his feet nicely and knocks it down to long on for one.
Floated up and around off, Nick uses his feet and defends it back to the bowler.
In the stumps, pushed back to the bowler.
Dragged length and around off, Nick Welch presses back and pushes it to cover.
Much full and on the pads, tucked away to mid-wicket.
Down the leg side, tickled down to deep fine leg for a run.
Loopy, full and around off, driven to covers off the front foot.
Tossed it up and around off, Nick Welch comes forward and shows the full face of the bat to defend it.
Around off, defended back to the bowler.
Much full and around middle, Nick Welch flicks it but straight to short leg.
Darts in on the pads, flicked away to deep backward square leg for a single.
On the pads, swept away to deep fine leg for one more.
And another! Full and around off, Nick reverse-sweeps it again to deep point this time for a single.

FIFTY FOR NICK WELCH! That has been a good inning! Full and around off, another reverse-sweep by Nick towards deep square leg for a couple of runs more to bring his milestone. Raises his bat and soaks up the applause.
Touch short and outside off, Nick Welch reverse-sweeps it to deep backward point for a couple of runs.
On middle, and the fuller length, Nick flicks it to mid-wicket off the front foot.
Sliding on the pads, tucked it to mid-wicket.
Dragged length and around middle, Craig looks to flick it off the back foot but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad. Could be going down leg.
Darts in, on the pads, flicked away to the left of the bowler, who stops it with a dive there.
Around off, defended back to the bowler off the front foot.
Slower, full and around off, Craig comes forward and defends it.
FOUR! Makes full use of a freebie! A full toss, outside off, Craig Ervine leans onto it and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Nagging length and around off, blocked out off the back foot.
Around off, blocked out towards cover.
On the pads, tucked away to deep square leg for one.
Floated up and around off, Craig comes forward to defend it but gets an outside edge that rolls away beside the pitch on the off side.
Around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and around off, Nick reverse-sweeps it towards backward point for one.
BEATEN! Tossed it up and outside off, drifts away from the batter, Nick Welch goes across to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full and outside off, driven to covers off the front foot.
A bit fuller and same line, around off, Craig Ervine prods forward and blocks it.
Switches to around the wicket, on a length and around off, blocked out towards cover.
Short of a length, but down the leg side, Craig lets it go to the keeper.
Hard length, over off, Craig defends it off the back foot.
On a good length and around off, Craig Ervine comes forward and blocks it.
Very full, pushed away to covers off the front foot.
Around off, blocked out off the front foot.
Dragged length and around middle, Nick turns it towards square leg.
A loopy ball, full and around off, Welch blocks it out.
Touch outside off, defended back to the bowler.
Darts in full and around off, Nick Welch goes across on his knees and sweeps it towards deep backward square leg for a couple of runs.
Aims the top of the off stump now, Craig defends it off the back foot towards short mid on.
Nagging length and around off, Craig taps it down to backward point off the back foot.
Sprays it on the pads, Craig lunges and looks to flick it but misses. Gets hit on the thigh pad.
Jags back in sharply, on the pads, and stays a low as well, Nick manages to bring his bat and flicks it off the inner half of the bat to square leg for one.
A bit of dragged down in the length and same line, outside off, Nick Welch gets inside the line and lets it go.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Nagging length and around off, dropped it down to cover off the back foot.
Much shorter and around middle, Craig presses back and punches it to extra cover.
Similar length, around off, Ervine comes forward and defends it.
Arounnd off, blocked out off the front foot.
Drags his length and around off, Craig Ervine goes back and defends it.
Darts in on the pads, tucked it to short mid-wicket off the front foot.
Similar delivery, outside off, Nick Welch shoulders his arms.
Outside off, left alone.
Touch short and around off, Nick defends it off the back foot.
Hard length and just outside off, Nick Welch goes back and looks to muscle it into the leg side. A proper dragged down shot but he misses and gets beaten on the inside edge of the bat.
Sliding on the pads, nudged it to square leg.

Back of a length and around off, Nick Welch rises with the bounce and looks to push it but gets surprised by extra bounce. The ball makes the connection with the upper side of the bat and goes aerially towards cover. Luckily for him, it falls down ahead of the fielder.
Nagging length and around off, Craig Ervine stats crouched and rolls his wrists to turn it towards short leg.
In the stumps, tucked away to mid-wicket.
Leg byes! Full and down the leg side, Ervine looks to tickle it but misses. The ball nudges his front pad and rolls away behind the wickets. Two runs for leg bye taken.
Full and outside off, Nick sweeps it to deep square leg for one.
Pushed away to covers off the front foot.
Tossed it up and around off, Nick Welch goes to defend it off the back foot but gets an inside edge that rolls away to short fine.
Full and around off, Craig Ervine looks to flick it but misses. The ball clips his back pad and rolls away towards square leg.
On the shorter side and around middle, Craig defends it of the back foot.

FOUR! That's a solid connection! Full and around off, Craig Ervine executes his slog sweep to perfection. The ball goes flat again and just touches the ropes. Third umpire is called in and he watches replays to confirm that it is a boundary as the ball has touched the grass before it made connection with the boundary cushions. Nonetheless, a good shot.
Nagging length, around off, blocked out off the front foot.

FOUR! DRAGGED! Floated up, too full and around off, Craig Ervine goes across on his knees and wants to take on the bowler. He goes to play a big slog sweep but ends up getting the connection off the inner half of the bat. Still, the ball goes flat and over the boundary towards deep mid-wicket on the bounce.
Full and around off, pushed away to the left of mid off for a quick single.
Sliding on the pads, Craig goes back and looks to tickle it into the leg side but misses. The ball clips his back pad and rolls away towards short leg.
Around off, blocked out.

That shoots up! Hard length, angling in, around middle, Craig Ervine gets cramped up and he looks to flick it away from his body. The ball takes an inside edge and hits the thigh pads and lobs up towards cover. The fielder, stationed there, moves quickly to his left but he ball falls down ahead of him.
Much full and outside off, Ervine drives it on the up but straight to backward point.
Touch full and same line, around off, Craig tries to push it off the front foot but gets it off the inner half of the bat to mid on.
Angles in, around off, Craig Ervine comes forward and blocks it.
Similar delivery and similar result.
Touch short and around off, Nick Welch presses back and punches it to cover.
On the pads, Nick uses his feet and drops it down to mid-wicket.

Tossed it up and around middle, comes in with the angle but turns away after pitching, Nick Welch comes forward and goes to play with the line but gets an outside edge that rolls away towards the slip.
Much straighter and around middle, Ervine drills it to long on for one.
Slower and outside off, Craig Ervine prods forward and blocks it.
Hard length, over middle, Nick Welch stays on the back foot and shows the full face of the bat to defend it solidly.
Nagging length and on the pads, turned away to backward short leg.
On the shorter side and around off, Nick punches it nicely from the back foot and finds the gap to the left of cover. Two runs taken.
Tries to target the stumps but ends up drifting it on the pads, Nick eased out to mid-wicket.

Touch short and outside off, Mulder goes back and punches it through covers for one.
On the pads, flicked away to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Errs in line and gets punished! Darts in full and down the leg side, Wiaan Mulder gently just tickles it off the back foot to deep fine leg for a boundary. Also, 300 up for South Africa.
Around off, defended back to the bowler off the front foot.
Nagging length and around middle, Lhuan-dre Pretorius turns it towards square leg and picks up another single.
On the pads, knocked it down to long on for one.
FOUR! Beautiful on-drive! Full and around middle, Lhuan-dre Pretorius prods forward and shows the full face of the bat to drive it to the left of the bowler for a glorious boundary.
Full and around middle, Wiaan Mulder clips it towards square leg and gets a single.
Back of a length and around off, Mulder goes back and punches it to cover.
Tucked it to mid-wicket off the front foot.
Excellent running between the wickets! Short of a length and around off, Wiaan Mulder presses back and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Hard length, on middle, Wiaan Mulder defends it off the back foot.
Darts in full and around middle, flicked it to mid-wicket off the front foot.
FOUR! Amazing hit! Tossed it up and around off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius uses his feet, gets to the pitch of the ball, and lofts it over the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Nagging length and around middle, pushed back to the bowler by Pretorius.
Full, drilled down to long off for one.
FOUR! THUMPED! A touch short, and around middle, Wiaan Mulder presses back quickly, opens his stance and pulls it disdainfully towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Outside off, sliced away to backward point by Mulder.

FOUR LEG BYES! Drifting on the pads, on the fuller length, Lhuan-dre Pretorius moves across a bit and looks to flick it but misses. The ball clips his front pad and goes to deep fine leg for a boundary.
On the pads, flicked away to deep square leg for one by Wiaan.
Leg bye! Full and around middle, Lhuan-dre Pretorius misses his flick again and the ball nudges his front pad and rolls away towards square leg. They take a leg bye.

Massive appeal for caught behind from the keeper and bowler but the umpire shakes his head. On a good length and down the leg side, Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets inside the line and looks to flick it, but gets beaten on the inside edge, and the ball clips his front pad and goes behind the wickets, where the keeper moves to his right and catches it.
Similar length, around off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets behind the line and defends it.
Hard length, down the leg side, Lhuan-dre Pretorius misses his tickle shot.
On the shorter side and around middle, Lhuan-dre Pretorius presses back and turns it to deep square leg for a single.
Floated up and around off, Wiaan Mulder stays leg side of the ball and drives it through covers for one.
Nagging length and around middle, tucked away to deep mid-wicket for one.
Full and around middle, defended back to the bowler.

Tossed it up and around middle, Lhuan-dre Pretorius comes forward and flicks it with soft hands in the gap towards deep mid-wicket. The fielder in the deep is a bit slow to get to the ball and throw it to the keeper and the batters take two runs.
Darts in on the pads, flicked it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! And another! Back of a length and outside off, Wiaan Mulder stays on the back foot, waits for it and guides it very late to deep third man for another boundary. Runs are coming thick and fast.

FOUR! SMACKED! Wiaan Mulder gets to 150 in just 167 balls. Such a class innings from a talented player! Hard length and around off, Mulder goes back a touch and pulls it hard to deep mid-wicket for a boundary to bring his milestone. Raises his bat to soak the applause.
Back of a length and around middle, Lhuan-dre Pretorius presses back and pulls it down to deep fine leg for a single.
Nagging length and on the pads, Lhuan-dre Pretorius blocks it.
On the good length and outside off, Wiaan Mulder taps it through cover point and takes a single. Also, 50 is up for this partnership in quick time.
Bowls it full and outside off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius comes forward and drives it to sweeper cover for one.
Slower, on the dragged length, around off, defended back to the bowler by Mulder.
Tossed it uup and outside off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius comes forward and knocks it down through covers for one.
On the pads, nudged it to short mid-wicket.
Full and around off, driven straight to cover off the front foot by Lhuan-dre Pretorius.
On the shorter side and outside off, Wiaan pushes it towards third man for one.
Nagging length and outside off, slower too, Mulder goes back and punches it but straight to cover.
Full and outside off, driven through covers for another single by Wiaan. 11 came off the first over after Tea. A nice start for South Africa.
FOUR! SMASHED! A bit short of a good length and angling into the batter, Wiaan Mulder shifts his weight to the back foot in a flash and pulls it hard down to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Nagging length and outside off, left alone.

BEATEN! Much better from Tanaka, as he drags his length and keeps it outside off, gets it to skid through the surface. Mulder swings his bat over the ball in order to go for another big shot downtown but misses and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Lands it full again and outside off this time, Wiaan Mulder leans onto it and drives it crisply through covers for a couple of runs.

FOUR! WOW! Some style to start the final session! A loosener from Tanaka Chivanga and gets punished! Sprays it on the pads and on the fuller length, Mulder comes forward and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius tucks this to short mid-wicket for another dot. That will be TEA ON DAY 1!
Fuller on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius flicks this to square leg for no run.
Short and on off, Wiaan Mulder cuts this to point for one.
Short of a length on off, Wiaan Mulder punches this to cover for no run.
Fuller on the pads, Lhuan-dre Pretorius flicks this through mid-wicket for one.
Fuller on the pads, Wiaan Mulder drills this to long on for one.
Good length wide of off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius leaves it.
Pitched up wide of off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets on top of it and drives this through cover for two runs.
Short-pitched, on middle and off. Wiaan Mulder pulls this flat towards deep mid-wicket and takes a single.
Full and wide outside off, Wiaan Mulder leaves it.
Full and on off, Wiaan Mulder thumps this to extra cover.

FOUR! Good length around off, Wiaan Mulder just aims to block this out. Gets an outside edge that drops on the second slip, and the ball slips underneath the fielder for a boundary towards the third man region.
Fuller on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius defends this out.

SIX! HIGH AND HANDSOME! Flighted on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets down on a knee and slog sweeps this right out of the middle of his bat. The ball sails way behind the fence and almost out of the park for a huge six.
Fuller around off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius thumps this on the bounce towards the bowler for no run.
FOUR! Authoritative from Lhuan-dre Pretorius. Tossed up around off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius dances down the track and smashes this through the gap between mid off and extra cover for four.
Fuller on off, Wiaan Mulder drives this through cover for one.
FOUR! A gentle drag down, on middle and leg, Wiaan Mulder rocks onto his back foot and pulls this up and over mid-wicket for four runs.
Good length on off, Wiaan Mulder pushes this through mid off for one.
Good length outside off, Wiaan Mulder leaves it.
FOUR! Poor from Tanaka Chivanga, as this was easy pickings for Wiaan Mulder. On a length, drifting down the leg. Wiaan Mulder leans inside and just tickles this fine to the keepers left for four.
Good length wide of off, Wiaan Mulder looks for the square cut but misses.
FOUR! Dishes one full and wide of off again. Wiaan Mulder this time, plants his front foot near the pitch of the delivery and nails the cover drive for four runs.
Lures the batter into the drive with a full one outside off. Wiaan Mulder goes for the expansive drive but gets beaten on the outside.
Tossed up on off, Wiaan Mulder drives this to long off for a single.
Quicker and fuller around off, Wiaan Mulder blocks this as well.
Fuller on off, Wiaan Mulder defends this one.
Floated around off, Wiaan Mulder blocks this one.
Tossed up wide of off, Wiaan Mulder drives this towards silly mid off for no run.
Fuller on off, Wiaan Mulder pushes this to silly mid on.
Back of a length, a lot closer to the stumps. Lhuan-dre Pretorius defends this well.
Touch fuller, but wide outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius leaves it as well.
Another one bowled short and wide of off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius shows no interest in throwing his bat at it.
Short and wide outside off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius leaves it.

OUT! The bowling change works for Zimbabwe. Good length, tailing back in a hint, David Bedingham prods in front and looks to punch this but gets beaten with the inwards movement and gets hit on his front pad. A gentle appeal is all that the umpire needed to raise his finger. David Bedingham misses out on a century as he is dismissed on 82.
David Bedingham lbw T Chivanga 82 (101b 7x4 0x6)
Full and way too wide down the leg.
Quicker and flatter on off, Wiaan Mulder punches this to point for another dot.
Tossed up on off, Wiaan Mulder pushes this towards cover for no run.
Short of a length on off, Wiaan Mulder smashes this to cover for no run.
Worked through mid-wicket for one and DB moves to 82.
Fuller on off, David Bedingham defends this towards cover.
Driven through cover for a single.
On a length around off, David Bedingham keeps it out on off.
Short and wide around off. David Bedingham punches this off his back foot but straight to cover.
Good length around off, David Bedingham gets behind it and defends this as well.
On a length around off again. DB blocks towards cover.
Good length on off, David Bedingham blocks this out on off.
Good length on the pads, Wiaan Mulder tucks this through mid-wicket and runs one.
Fuller around off, David Bedingham keeps it out with a block as well.
Flighted on off, David Bedingham gets on top of it and blocks this as well.
Tossed up around off, David Bedingham blocks this out.
Fuller on off, David Bedingham defends this one.

That's much more like it. Drifting in, turning away from the batter and in the line of stumps. David Bedingham goes for the sweep but misses. A loud appeal for LBW, but the umpire remains unmoved, hinting that this was going over.
Good length on off, David Bedingham defends this out.

FOUR! Another one timed too well and in the gap for four. Short-pitched, on middle and off. Wiaan Mulder moves a shade to his leg and pulls this to the left of mid-wicket and gets a boundary to end the over.
Short-pitched, outside off. Wiaan Mulder leaves it.
Back of a length around off, David Bedingham smashes this to sweeper cover for one.
Good length around the pads, David Bedingham looks for the nudge on the leg side but misses.
On a length around the pads, Wiaan Mulder flicks this through backward square leg for one. Also, 200 up for South Africa.
Good length on middle and leg. Wiaan Mulder pushes this to silly mid on.
Much slower, on off. David Bedingham jams this away to silly point.
Length dragged back on middle and off. Wiaan Mulder rocks back and punches this to long on for a single.
Tossed up on off, Wiaan Mulder blocks this as well.
Short of a length on off, Wiaan Mulder defends this one.
Quicker on off, Wiaan Mulder defends this out.
Yet another couple as Wiaan Mulder flicks this to deep mid-wicket.
Flicked through mid-wicket and the batters take two more. Runs are not hard to get for these two out in the middle and this is what Zimbabwe need to think about.
Short-pitched, wide of off. David Bedingham lets it sail back to the keeper.
Back of a length around off, David Bedingham hops up on his toes and punches this through cover for two.
FOUR! Thread that tiny little gap behind square on leg for four. Short-pitched, around leg. David Bedingham pulls this flat and wide of backward square leg to his right for four.
Good length, down the leg. David Bedingham leaves it.
Bumper, around leg. David Bedingham sits under it.
Tossed up on off, Wiaan Mulder blocks this out.
Pushed through on middle and off, Wiaan Mulder pushes this back to the bowler.
A lot fuller, outside off. Wiaan Mulder blocks this out.
Short and wide outside off and with cover positioned deep it is a an easy single for DB.
Quicker and flatter on off, Wiaan Mulder punches this off his back foot and takes a single.
Tossed up on off, Wiaan Mulder defends this out.
Persist with the short-pitched delivery ploy, DB pulls this flat to the right of deep square and takes two this time.

CENTURY FOR WIAAN MULDER! Blessing Muzarabani bowls a short-pitched delivery again and Wiaan Mulder pulls this to a slightly backward square leg for a single to bring up his century. Back-to-back centuries for Wiaan Mulder in this series. Quite an authoritative inning this from the South African skipper.
Short-pitched, on middle and leg, David Bedingham pulls this to deep square and takes one. Brings Mulder on strike as he is just 1 away of his century.
Good length on off, David Bedingham pushes this to cover for no run.
WIDE! Bumper, way too high for the umpire's liking. Wided.
Back of a length around middle and off, David Bedingham mistimes the pull but does enough to get it through mid-wicket for two.
Goes full and on middle and leg. Wiaan Mulder tucks this through square leg for one.
Good length on off, David Bedingham punches this on the up towards mid off for no run.
Drags the length back a bit, on the pads. Bedingham tucks this to mid-wicket.
On a length around the pads, David Bedingham flicks it uppishly but short of short mid-wicket.
Back of a length around the pads, Wiaan Mulder flicks this through square leg for one.

FOUR! South African skipper moves to 97 with this boundary. Pitched-up, outside off. Wiaan Mulder punches onto it and drives this back past the bowler in a flash with a bit of arrogance behind it for four runs.
Full and wide down the leg. Wiaan Mulder goes for the flick but misses.
Pitches it short, on off. Wiaan Mulder pulls this to deep square for one.
Goes a little fuller again, on leg. David Bedingham tucks this through square leg for one.
Good length around off, David Bedingham defends this out.
Goes full and on off, David Bedingham pushes this towards silly mid off for no run.

In the air... safe. Blessing Muzarabani puts in an extra bit of effort and darts a well-directed bumper towards Wiaan Mulder. The SA skipper looks to bail out of the pull but ends up top-edging this in the air, but in between square leg and long leg for one.
Good length on top of off, Wiaan Mulder dabs this to the slip cordon.
Short and wide on off, David Bedingham cuts this to point for no run.
Quicker one around off, Wiaan Mulder drives this through cover for one.
Tossed up on off, Wiaan Mulder defends this out.
Punched towards silly mid off for no run.
LEG BYE! Tossed up, down the leg. David Bedingham misses on the sweep and gets it clipped off the pads to fine leg for one.
Fuller, down the leg. David Bedingham looks to hit this over mid on but gets an inside edge and gets it rolled through square leg for two.
Short and wide around off. WM looks to cut this through gully but chops this on the bounce back to the keeper.
Good length on off, Wiaan Mulder punches this to mid off.
FOUR! Goes full and wide outside off. Wiaan Mulder gets right on top of the delivery and nails the cover drive to perfection and adds four more to the tally.
Good length around off, Wiaan Mulder blocks this out.

FOUR! Takudzwanashe Kaitano messes up a simple stop and what should have been a couple turns into a boundary. Short and wide outside off, Wiaan Mulder plays this late, hops up on his toss, rolls his wrists over it and finds the gap through backward point. Takudzwanashe Kaitano running to his left, dives a bit too early and the ball goes to the fence for four.
On a length around the pads, David Bedingham nudges this through mid-wicket for one.
Much slower, on off. Wiaan Mulder defends this out.
Fuller on middle and off, David Bedingham flicks this through mid on for one.
FOUR! Dragged down, wide outside off. David Bedingham rocks back and cuts this wide and fine to the left of point and the ball has raced to the fence for four. Easy pickings for DB.
Fuller on the pads, David Bedingham flicks this through mid-wicket and fetches himself a brace.
Shouts of catch it but Mulder pushes this wide to the left of short mid on, off his back foot and takes one.
Full and on off, Wiaan defends it.
Hits the hard length, on top of off. David punches this to cover for no run.
Full, too much width to play with. Wiaan Mulder strides to the pitch of the delivery and drives this to sweeper cover for one.
On a length around off, Wiaan Mulder blocks it out.
Good length on middle and off, David Bedingham flicks this away through square leg for a single.
Back of a length, around leg. Wiaan Mulder pulls this towards long leg and takes a single.
Short and wide outside off, David Bedingham punches this off the back foot for a single towards sweeper cover.
Short and wide around off, Wiaan Mulder punches this towards extra cover's left for a dot.
Dished fuller on off, DB drills this down to long off for a single.
Fuller on off, David Bedingham punches this back to the bowler.
Tossed up, wide outside off. David Bedingham gets on top of it and blocks this out.
Fuller on the pads, David Bedingham sweeps this to fine leg for a couple.
Quicker and flatter around off, Wiaan Mulder rocks back and pushes this through mid on for one.
Nagging length and around off, David Bedingham pushes it back to the bowler.
Down the leg side, tickled down to deep fine leg for one by Mulder.
Hard length, over leg, Wiaan Mulder goes back and clips it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! Touch shot! Back of a length and outside off, Wiaan Mulder stays deep in his crease and plays this late cut towards deep backward point. The deep point fielder runs across to his left and even puts in a dive but couldn't save the boundary.
Full and around middle, defended towards square leg.
Short of a good length and around off, Wiaan Mulder presses back and drags it to deep backward square leg for a couple.

Dropped! A bit fuller and flighted, outside off, Wiaan Mulder goes back and looks to punch it but gets an outside edge that flies to the first slip, where the fielder quickly moves to his right but can't hold onto this low catch. It rolls away towards short third and they take a single.

Sublime fifty for David Bedingham. What an inning from a class player, as he has changed the course of the game with his inning. From playing attacking shots to rotating the strike, he has done everything. Full and around off, David pushes it towards cover to bring his milestone with a single.
Dragged length and outside off, David Bedingham presses back and punches it through covers. The sweeper cover makes a fumble in the deep and the batter take two runs.
Slower, full and around off, defended back to the bowler.
Nagging length and outside off, David Bedingham guides it to the left of backward point for a couple of runs.
Tossed it up but down the leg side, David Bedingham goes to tickle it fine but misses. The keeper collects it to his left and appeals for caught behind but the umpire shakes his head.
Hard length, over middle, Wiaan Mulder shows the full face of the bat to defend it solidly.
Short of a length and around off, David Bedingham swivels and pulls it down to deep square leg for one.
Tempting length and on the pads, tucked away to mid-wicket off the front foot.
Full and around off, David comes forward and knocks it down to mid off.
Back of a length and wide outside off, Wiaan Mulder rises with the bounce and cuts it to deep point for a run.
A bit short and around middle, David goes across and clips it to the right of mid on, where the fielder fumbles and the batters take a single, seeing the opportunity.
Dragged length and outside off, Wiaan Mulder presses back and punches it through covers for a couple of runs. That brings up 100 runs off just 109 balls for this partnership.
On the pads, tucked it to mid-wicket off the front foot.
Full and around off, Mulder drives it short mid off.
Tossed it up and around off, Mulder comes forward and defends it.
Nagging length and outside off, David Bedingham punches it through covers for a single.
A bit short and outside off, Wiaan Mulder goes back and cuts it down through covers for one.
Short delivery, around off, Wiaan Mulder goes back and pulls it down to deep square leg for one.
Outside off, patted down to backward point off the back foot.

Oh, that stayed low! On a length and just outside off, the ball stays much low than Mulder would have expected it to be. He goes across and looks to drag it into the leg side but gets beaten on the inside edge.
Back of a length, on the top of the off stump, Mulder rises with the bounce and drops it down to cover.
On a good length and around the fifth stump line, Mulder covers his off stump and lets it go.
FOUR! Hit disdainfully! Short of a good length and around middle, sits up nicely for the batter, Wiaan Mulder shifts his weight to the back foot and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Nagging length and around off,  David Bedingham goes back and punches it to cover.
Floated up and outside off, Wiaan Mulder comes forward and drives it through covers for one.
Around off, driven to short mid off.
Full and around off, Mulder pushes it to extra cover.
Flighted, full and around off, Wiaan Mulder comes forward and drives it to short covers.
Outside off, eased out to long off for one by David off the front foot.

A stifled appeal for caught behind by the keeper but the umpire shakes his head! Back of a length and down the leg side, Wiaan Mulder swivels and looks to hook it but gets a bit late in his shot. The ball goes past his left shoulder and the keeper collects it to his left.
Hard length, over off, David goes across and tucks it wide of mid-wicket for one. First run after Lunch.
Nagging length and in that channel outside off, David Bedingham plants his front leg forward and shows the full face of the bat to defend it solidly.
A bit fuller and around off, David Bedingham comes forward and drives it back to the bowler, who leaps and gets both his hands. The ball rolls away towards  mid on.
Back of a length and outside off, David Bedingham chops it out to gully off the back foot.
Much full and around off, David Bedingham gets across and looks to flick it but gets a leading edge towards cover.
Quicker and flatter on off, Wiaan Mulder punches this firmly towards cover for no run. That will be LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Pushed through on off, Wiaan Mulder blocks this out.
Short and wide on off, David Bedingham rocks back and punches this to a widish long off for a single.
Fuller and flatter, around off. Wiaan Mulder pushes this to sweeper cover for one.
Quicker and flatter on off, David Bedingham rolls this to long on for a single.
Pushed through on middle and off, David Bedingham pushes this to silly mid on.
This was much shorter from Tanaka Chivanga and David Bedingham hops up on his toes and pushes this to Kaitano at sweeper cover for a single.
Back of a length around off, David Bedingham hops onto his back foot and punches this to sweeper cover for two this time.
On a length around off, Wiaan Mulder pushes this away for a single.

FOUR! Sloppy in the field as Takudzwanashe Kaitano gives away a couple of extra runs here. Short and wide outside off, Wiaan Mulder smashes this towards deep point's right. Takudzwanashe Kaitano runs to his right, and puts in a slide in an attempt to field this, but slides over the ball, and the ball goes to the fence for four.
On a length, on off. Wiaan Mulder blocks this out.
Good length, wide outside off. Wiaan Mulder shoulders arms it.
Flighted wide of off, David Bedingham gets on top of the delivery and jams this out on off.
Quicker and flatter, wide outside off, Wiaan Mulder pushes this to sweeper cover for one.
Much slower, on off, Wiaan Mulder defends this off his front foot.
Pushed through on middle and leg, David Bedingham punches this down to long on for a single.
Tossed up around off, Wiaan Mulder punches this towards silly mid off. The fielder fails to field this clean as the ball deflects off his hands to long on for a single.
Short of a length wide outside off, David Bedingham punches this through extra cover for one.
Short of a length and around off, David Bedingham goes back and pulls it down to deep square leg for one.
Full and around off, David Bedingham pushes it towards cover off the front foot.
A bit fuller and a touch outside off, David Bedingham moves across and shows the full face of the bat to keep it down towards mid on.
Hard length and around off, Wiaan Mulder pats it down to deep point for one.
An appeal for LBW but is turned down! On a good length, sliding on the pads, Wiaan Mulder comes forward to flick it but misses and gets hit on the front pad. Could be going down leg.
A yorker, around off, Wiaan Mulder jams it out to mid off.
Slower through the air, full and around off, David Bedingham pushes it towards cover point off the front foot.
FOUR! AMAZING HIT! Touch full and around middle, David Bedingham clears out his front leg away and thumps it over mid on for a boundary.
Full and around off, Wiaan Mulder comes forward and knocks it down to wide long off for one.
On the pads, nudged it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR WIAAN MULDER! What a class inning from the skipper, as he is leading from the front. Darts in quick, full and on the pads, Mulder sweeps it to deep backward square leg for a boundary to bring his milestone. Second fifty plus score for him in this 2-match series.
Around off, driven to covers off the front foot.
Short of a length and around off, Wiaan Mulder pulls it down to deep square leg for a single.
Hard length and around off, jags back in, Wiaan Mulder hops back to tuck but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
On a good length and around middle, David Bedingham swivels and pulls it aerially to the left of square leg for one.
On the shorter side and around off, Mulder pulls it down to deep square leg for one more.
Back of a length, around middle, stays a bit low, Wiaan Mulder gets squared up but manages to keep it out towards mid-wicket.
Hard length, over middle, David Bedingham gets inside the line and tickles it to deep fine leg for one.
Keeps it shorter and around off, Mulder drops it down towards cover.
Dragged length and around off, Wiaan Mulder blocks it.
Touch short and outside off, Wiaan Mulder pats it down towards backward point, who moves to his left and cuts it off.
Around off, pushed away to covers.
Nagging length and around off, Wiaan Mulder goes back and punches it to mid on.
Tossed it up, around off, Wiaan Mulder comes forward and defends it.
Hard length, over middle, Wiaan Mulder swivels on his toes and drags it to deep square leg for one.
On the pads, flicked away towards mid-wicket for one.
Short-pitched, around off, Wiaan Mulder goes back and pulls it aerially to deep square leg for one.
On a good length and down the leg side, Wiaan Mulder moves across and leaves it.

Back of a length, angling in, around middle, the ball shoots up off the deck and follows the batter, David Bedingham gets into an awkward position but manages to flick it towards square leg. A single taken.
Hard length and outside off, David Bedingham moves across and sways away from it.
FOUR! TOP SHOT! Back of a length and just outside off, Wiaan Mulder rises with the bounce and punches it through extra covers for a boundary.
Nagging length and outside off, Wiaan Mulder watches it carefully and lets it go to the keeper.
FOUR! DEFT TOUCH! Full but down the leg side, Wiaan Mulder gets inside the line and just tickles it fine to deep fine leg for a boundary. Also, 50 is up for this partnership.
Hard length and outside off, Wiaan Mulder comes forward and just taps it with soft hands. The ball goes through the gap beside the gully fielder and they take two runs.
Dragged length and around middle, David Bedingham chips it towards mid on and picks up a single.
Lands it full and around off, David Bedingham comes forward and drives it to mid off.
Back of a length and around off, Wiaan Mulder blocks it.
FOUR! Boundaries are coming thick and fast for the Proteas. Yet another short-pitched delivery and Wiaan Mulder has pulled this right in the gap behind square on leg for four more runs.
Another bouncer, Wiaan Mulder sits under it.
Another one, pitched short around middle and leg, Wiaan Mulder pulls this towards deep square and takes two.
Bumper, around off. Wiaan Mulder ducks down.
Short-pitched, down the leg, David Bedingham helps this towards fine leg for a single.
Hits the hard length on off, Wiaan Mulder jams this out.
Good length around off, Wiaan Mulder gets right on top of the delivery and blocks it out.
Touch fuller around off, Wiaan Mulder leaves it all alone.
Good length around off, Wiaan Mulder defends this off his front foot.
FOUR! GLORIOUS! Pitched up around off, Wiaan Mulder plants his front foot towards the line of the delivery and nails the off-drive to perfection for a boundary down the ground.

SIX! WIAAN CLEARS THE ROPES WITH EASE! Back of a length around middle and off, Wiaan Mulder picks the length up early and settles well within the line of the delivery and pulls this up and over the fence towards deep mid-wicket region for a biggie.
Back of a length around off, David Bedingham hops up on his toes and punches this through cover for two.
On a length wide outside off, David Bedingham punches this to cover for no run.
On a length around the pads, Wiaan Mulder flicks this through square leg and takes a single.
On a length around off, Wiaan Mulder defends this off his front foot towards cover.
Good length around off, Wiaan Mulder defends this off his front foot.

FOUR! Another one pulled well but this time by Wiaan Mulder. Short-pitched, on middle and off. Wiaan Mulder gets onto his back foot and pulls this over square leg for four runs. The skipper of SA is looking rock solid.
Good length, wide outside off, David Bedingham pushes at it but gets beaten on the outside.

FOUR! Third on a trot and this was a lot more convincing from David Bedingham. Back of a length, around middle and leg, David Bedingham settles well behind it and pulls this up and over the fielder at mid-wicket for third boundary of the over.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries but DB was fortunate on this occasion. On a length, right around off. David Bedingham presses forward and looks to punch this firmly towards mid off but gets an outside edge and the ball has just evaded the second slip fielder diving to his right for a boundary.

FOUR! Excellently placed, right in the gap for four. Short-pitched, on off. David Bedingham hops up on his toes and cuts this wide to the left of point and the ball has raced to the fence for four. David Bedingham has injected a bit of aggression since his arrival in the middle.
On a length around off, David Bedingham defends this solidly off the front foot.
Good length on off, David Bedingham gets right behind the line of it and defends this out.
On a length, wide outside off. Wiaan Mulder drops this short of gully for a dot.
Good length around off again, Wiaan Mulder guides this to second slip for no run.
Good length around off, David Bedingham punches this through cover for a single.
On a length around off, David Bedingham dabs this to the slip cordon for no run.
Good length on the pads, David Bedingham flicks this through square leg for a couple.
FOUR! Back of a length around off. David Bedingham hops up on his toes and looks to punch this firmly but gets an outside edge that rolls past gully for a boundary.
Hard length and around off, David Bedingham pushes it to deep point for one off the back foot to open his account.

OUT! PLUMB LBW! Wellington Masakadza strikes now and the debutant goes for just 3 runs. Tossed it up and around off and middle, gets to slide in with the angle and much fuller, Lesego Senokwane goes on his knees and looks to sweep it. As the ball is too close to the body, he misses his shot and gets rapped on the front pad. The appeals go up and the umpire raises his finger. Zimbabwe have been brilliant this morning as they have taken two wickets within the first hour. South Africa are 24/2.
Lesego Senokwane lbw W Masakadza 3 (36b 0x4 0x6)
Full and around off, Lesego Senokwane defends it back to the bowler.
Around off, driven towards cover for one by Mulder.
Floated, full and around off, Wiaan Mulder pushes it to mid on.
Tossed it up, around off, Wiaan Mulder comes forward and defends it right under his eyes.
On a good length and around off, Lesego Senokwane defends it.
Nagging length and around off, Lesego Senokwane goes back and blocks it.
Hard length, over off, Lesego Senokwane drops it down to cover point off the back foot.

Good effort in the field! Fuller and around off, Wiaan Mulder leans onto it and drives it to the left of the bowler. Though he hasn't got it off the middle of the bat but the ball goes in the gap. Wellington Masakadza goes after it from covers and he slides in the end to flick it inside the field. Three runs taken.
Back of a length and outside off, left alone.
Lands it full and outside off, Wiaan Mulder leaves it.
Around off, driven towards mid off for a quick single by Mulder.
On the shorter side and outside off, Wiaan Mulder slices it to deep backward point for a couple of runs off the back foot.
Dragged length and around off, Wiaan Mulder presses back and punches it to cover.
Floated up and around off, driven to cover off the front foot.
Turns away, on the fuller side and around off, Mulder comes forward and blocks it.
FOUR! DRILLED! A nice juicy over-pitched ball, around middle, Wiaan Mulder comes forward and whips it off the pads to deep square leg for a boundary.
Full and outside off, left alone by Lesego Senokwane.
Back of a length and around middle, Lesego Senokwane clips it through square leg for a couple of runs.
Full and around off, Lesego Senokwane comes forward and drives it back to the bowler.
Similar delivery, outside off, left alone again.
A bit fuller and outside off, left alone by Lesego Senokwane.
A sharp bouncer, around off, comes in from wide of the crease. Lesego Senokwane rises with the bounce and looks to cut it but gets deceived by the extra bounce and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Hard length and outside off, Mulder stays on the back foot and cuts it but straight to backward point. A wicket-maiden for Tanaka Chivanga.
Back of a length and around off, Wiaan Mulder watchfully leaves it.
On a good length and outside off, Wiaan Mulder leaves it again.
Outside off, left alone by Mulder.
Nagging length and around off, Mulder blocks it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Tanaka Chivanga draws first blood for Zimbabwe and Tony de Zorzi departs for 10(30). Bowls it on the hard length and outside off, and gets it to come back in from wide of the crease, also gets that step bounce off the deck. Tony rises with the bounce and goes to cut it, but the ball is close to his body, which he wouldn't have anticipated. Also, he fails to judge that extra bounce. As he tries to force his cut shot, the ball catches the outer half of the bat and goes towards backward point, where Nick Welch takes this sharp catch around his face height. South Africa are 11/1.
Tony de Zorzi c N Welch b T Chivanga 10 (30b 2x4 0x6)
MAIDEN! Again full and around off, Lesego Senokwane pushes it to mid on off the front foot.
Full and outside off, left alone by Lesego.
BEATEN! A fuller one now and just outside off, moves away, Lesego Senokwane comes forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge again.
Lovely delivery! Short-pitched, around off, Lesego Senokwane tries to sway away from it, but the ball follows him and beats the outside edge of the bat.
Back of a length and around off, Lesego Senokwane presses back and punches it to point.
On a good length and around off, Lesego Senokwane looks to flick but misses and gets rapped on the front pad. There is a mild appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes his head. Height could be the issue.
Short of a length and down the leg side, Tony de Zorzi misses his tickle shot.
Bowls it full and outside off, Tony de Zorzi throws his hands and plays this drive shot far from his body. Doesn't get off the middle of the bat and the ball rolls away to cover.
Nagging length and around off, Tony de Zorzi covers his off stump and blocks it.
Hard length, over off, Tony de Zorzi gets inside the line and defends it.
Angling in, on the pads, eased out to mid on.
Back of a length and around off, Tony de Zorzi blocks it off the back foot.
A bouncer, around off, ducks underneath it.

This is a solid defence! Hard length and around off, Lesego Senokwane plants his front leg forward and shows the full face of the bat to make a connection off the middle of the bat. The ball rolls away to cover.
Around off, defended it to covers off the front foot.

Lovely delivery! A bit fuller and outside off, threatens to come in but gets straightened up after hitting the deck, Lesego Senokwane gets squared up as he looks to defend and gets beaten on the outside edge.

Luck again for South Africa. On a hard length and angling in, around off, gets a step bounce off the deck, Lesego Senokwane goes back and looks to flick it and closes the bat face early. The ball comes a bit later and gets a leading edge to lob up beside the pitch on the off side. The bowler, Blessing Muzarabani, himself goes after it and runs across to his left, but the ball lands down before he can reach there. Lucky escape for the debutant as it could have gone anywhere.
Back of a length and around off, Lesego Senokwane rises with the bounce and defends it.
On a good length and around off, Tony de Zorzi leaves it.

FOUR! GLORIOUS! This surely will give confidence to Tony de Zorzi. Much full and around off, Tony lunges and shows the full face of the bat to drive it through the line down the ground to the right of the bowler for a boundary.
Much full and around off, driven to cover off the front foot.

Hard length and around off, Tony de Zorzi comes forward and pushes it with soft hands. Gets it off the outer half of the bat, but the ball doesn't carry to the gully fielder as it has been played with soft hands. Dribbles away to him who collects it.
Dragged length and outside off, Tony de Zorzi leaves it.
Bowls it full and around off, Tony de Zorzi drives it towards cover, who fumbles but the ball goes nowhere.
Short of a length and around off, gets an extra bounce off the deck, Lesego Senokwane sways away from it. Another maiden for Blessing Muzarabani.
Down the leg side, Lesego Senokwane leaves it.
Outside off, left alone.
Nagging length and outside off, Lesego Senokwane leaves it.
Around off, dabs it down towards gully off the outer half of the bat.
On a good length and around off, Lesego Senokwane blocks it.
Nagging length and around off, defended back to the bowler.

DROPPED! Sean Williams is the culprit! Hard length and just outside off, shaping away a bit, Tony de Zorzi throws his hands at it and looks to cut it but gets a big outside edge that flies towards the first slip. But Williams flies to his left from the second slip and tries to take it but the ball pops out of his hands and goes behind the wickets. They take two runs and how costly it will prove? If Sean hadn't attempted to go there, this could have been a straightforward catch for the first slip, where Craig Ervine could have taken it, as it was on the good height.
Full and around off, shaping away a touch, Tony de Zorzi comes forward to defend but gets an outside edge that rolls away to gully.
Hard length and angling in, around middle, Tony gets cramped up for room and looks to tuck it but gets an inside edge to mid-wicket.
Back of a length and around off, Tony de Zorzi gets on top of the bounce and punches it to cover.
Starts off with a fuller length and outside off, Tony de Zorzi leaves it alone.
A bit fuller and around off, Lesego Senokwane shows the full face of the bat to defend it off the front foot and gets an inside edge that goes on the bounce to backward short leg.
Oh, that has jagged back in sharply, on a nagging length and around off, Lesego Senokwane comes forward to defend but gets an inside edge onto his thigh pads.
On a good length and around off, Lesego gets on top of the bounce and blocks it.
Hard length, over off, Lesego Senokwane taps it towards backward point and wants to have a quick single but is sent back. He is looking a bit tentative.
Back of a length but down the leg side, Lesego Senokwane sways away from it and leaves it.
Hard length, angling in, around off, Lesego Senokwane goes back and turns it to backward short leg.
Attacks the stumps now, Tony blocks it.

FOUR! SLICED! Much fuller and outside off, invites the batter for a drive and Tony de Zorzi lunges and looks to drive towards cover. He gets it off the outer half of the bat and the ball goes to the right of backward point for a boundary.
Lands it full again and outside off, Tony de Zorzi shoulders his arms.
Fuller and seaming in, around off, Tony de Zorzi comes forward and drives it to mid off.
From around the wicket, hard length and around off, Tony de Zorzi gets inside the line and defends it towards the bowler.

Begins with a very full delivery, almost a yorker, around leg, Lesego Senokwane leans onto and flicks it to deep fine leg for a single to get his first runs in Test cricket. Also, the inning of South Africa get underway.
Ends with a back-of-a-length ball, angling in, around off, Tony de Zorzi rises with the bounce and blocks it. Maiden!
Goes full but down the leg side, Tony looks to flick it but misses.
Nagging length and around off, Tony de Zorzi defends it into the pitch off the back foot.
Switches to around the wicket, bowls it on the back of a length and angles it into the body of the batter, Tony de Zorzi gets cramped up for room but manages to drop it down towards mid-wicket.
Again a short-pitched ball, around off, Tony de Zorzi sways away from it.
Starts off with a bouncer, around leg, Tony de Zorzi ducks underneath it.
